[{'comment_id': 1346946993, 'comment_body': 'why do we need a `unique_ptr` here?
why not just use the completion wrapper?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 5, 7, 41, 34, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'yuvalif', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1347714171, 'comment_body': 'i really like the use of [RAII](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/raii) to handle this cleanup 👍

but `RgwAioCompletionWrapper` is essentially just reinventing [std::unique_ptr](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/memory/unique_ptr). if we add a custom deleter for `AioCompletion`, we can use `std::unique_ptr` directly:
```c++
// unique_ptr deleter that calls release()
struct AioCompletionDeleter {
  void operator()(librados::AioCompletion* c) { c->release(); }
};
using aio_completion_ptr = std::unique_ptr<librados::AioCompletion, AioCompletionDeleter>;
```
callers could either construct this ptr directly:
```c++
  aio_completion_ptr c{librados::Rados::aio_create_completion(nullptr, nullptr)};
```
or we could add a helper function that returns `aio_completion_ptr`:
```c++
  auto c = make_aio_completion(nullptr, nullptr);
```
what do you think?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 10, 5, 16, 46, 9, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cbodley', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1423699777, 'comment_body': '@cbodley could you please re-review?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 12, 12, 9, 19, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'yuvalif', 'type': 'User'}]

